{
  "stem": "21139.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And he didn't even realize that-- I mean, he knew he was going to England.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And my parents told him that he was going to see my sister and my-- and my brother Julius.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And so-- as he told me not so long ago that when my father took him to the train and he went with the Kindertransport to England, he never realized that-- he thought it was just a train ride with my father, never realizing that he would not see his parents again.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "[CRYING]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We went to school that-- to Pforzheim, Siegie and I with my father, who always took us every day.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he-- we went as-- when we went to the school, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we were sent home, because in Pforzheim, the-- by the time we came to school, the synagogues were burning already.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we returned home.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But my father, my father went to the business.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- but Siegie and I went home.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And as we arrived into Konigsbach-- and the-- the train station was a little bit elevated.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we looked to our right.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We saw the-- the synagogue burning.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we-- and as we walked down the hill, we saw the Torahs on the ground.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We went home.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[SOBBING] And my mother was standing at the window, waiting for-- looking out for-- to see if we are-- that we got home.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "She knew what was going on.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we came to the house.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And my mother, she didn't know what to do, where to take us for safety, because they-- the few families that were still in Konigsbach, the Jewish families, they destroyed the homes completely.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
